A review of the current appointment procedure is ongoing and the matter will be considered further on completion. The review is wide-ranging and includes consideration of the following issues:- the need to ensure and protect the principle of judicial independence;
- eligibility for appointment;
- composition of the Judicial Appointments Advisory Board;
- the appointments process;
- accountability in respect of its functioning; and
- promoting equality and diversity.Any proposal to revise the current system of judicial appointments would involve amendment of the legislation and would, of course, be a matter for consideration by Government in due course.
